The paper deals with the problem of optimal attacking strategies in cognitive radio networks, which involves spectrum sensing and dynamic decision-making. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the optimization of attacking strategies in the presence of randomized feedback graphs, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
